(classical) commutation relations:
 

The reparametrization invariance of the string becomes, in the bit
language, the invariance with respect to the symmetry group 
of permutations of the labels . The whole permutation group
 is split into equivalence classes  of permutations
having the same number of cycles with fixed lengths
, . Then, the Hilbert space of the
quantized model can be split, according to this, into a direct sum
of twisted sectors  , associated with each
conjugacy class . The transformations inside a conjugacy
class reduces to relabelling of bits in the cycles. Therefore, the
twisted sector corresponding to the conjugacy class 
with  cycles, can be identified with the -string Hilbert
space. In particular, one string sector corresponds to cyclic
subgroups of , and up to relabelling of  is given by
 

